# FUNCTIONS ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
amort_form <- function(pbal_tz_zz, pbal_zz, ann_r_zz, term_zz, in_grace_per_zz = 0) {
  mon_r <- ann_r_zz/12
  mon_n <- term_zz
  num <- mon_r * (1+mon_r)^mon_n
  den <- (1+mon_r)^mon_n -1 
  payment <- pbal_tz_zz * num / den # payment is determined only at the starting balance? 
  r_accr <- pbal_zz * mon_r
  bal_pmt <- payment - r_accr
  
  int_pmt <- r_accr
  
  if(in_grace_per_zz == 1){
    payment <- 0 
    bal_pmt <- 0 
    int_pmt <- 0 
  }
  new_pbal <- pbal_zz + r_accr - payment
  
  return(c(round(payment,2),round(bal_pmt,2) , round(int_pmt,2), round(r_accr,2), round(new_pbal,2)))
}

amort_form(102240.11,102240.11,.15,48-3)


amort_time_form <- function(start_date_zz,  pbal_zz, ann_r_zz, term_zz, grace_period_zz = 3) {
  pbal_tz_zz <-   pbal_zz
  mon_r <- ann_r_zz/12
  mon_n <- term_zz
  num <- mon_r * (1+mon_r)^mon_n
  den <- (1+mon_r)^mon_n -1 
  payment <- pbal_tz_zz * num / den
  r_accr <- pbal_zz * mon_r
  bal_pmt <- payment - r_accr
  
  new_pbal <- pbal_zz + r_accr - payment
  #return(new_pbal)
  new_pbal <- pbal_tz_zz
  
  amort_df <- data.frame(
    month = 0
    #, date = as.Date(start_date_zz)
    , payment = 0
    , principal = 0
    , interest = 0
    , interest_accrued = 0 
    , balance = pbal_tz_zz
  )
  
  i <- 1
  #d <- 
  
  while ( i <= term_zz) {
    
    
    if(i <=grace_period_zz) {
      in_grace <- 1
      term <- term_zz
    } else if (i == grace_period_zz +1) {
      # In this period we recalculate monthly payment
      pbal_tz_zz <- as.numeric(amort_df$balance[nrow(amort_df)])
      term <- term_zz - grace_period_zz 
      in_grace <-0
    } else {
      in_grace <-0
    }
    
    
    
    # Create the next line and add it on to existing data
    newrow <- amort_form(pbal_tz_zz, new_pbal,ann_r_zz,term, in_grace_per_zz =in_grace)
    newrow <- c(i,newrow)
    #, '2000-01-01' 
    amort_df <- rbind(amort_df,newrow)
    
    # can't get the dates to work right
    #amort_df$date[i] <- as.Date(ymd(as.Date(start_date_zz))) %m+% months(i-1)
    
    # Reset the starting balance
    new_pbal <- as.numeric(amort_df$balance[nrow(amort_df)])
    i <- i + 1
  }
  
  # Dates are still wonky
  #amort_df$date[term_zz] <- as.Date(ymd(as.Date(start_date_zz))) %m+% months(term_zz-1)
  
  # formats are also wonky
  amort_df <- amort_df %>%
    mutate(payment = as.numeric(payment)
           , principal = as.numeric(principal)
           , interest = as.numeric(interest)
           , balance = as.numeric(balance) 
    )
  return(amort_df)
}

# Test 
#amort_time_form('2000-01-01',98500,.15,48, grace_period_zz = 3)


nii_table_fun <- function( enganche_zz, legal_fees_zz, op_de_comp_est_pct_zz
                           , ann_rate_zz, loan_term_zz, grace_period_zz, markup_zz, down_payment_pct_zz
                           , seguro_est_pct_zz , seguro_defl_rate_zz
                           , maint_premium_zz, maint_cost_per_visit_pct_zz, maint_infl_zz
                           , costo_activo_zz,  costs_zz, iva_rate_zz = 0.12 , albedo_wacc_zz, risk_free_rate_zz){
  
  
  # Calculated Fields  
  maint_cost_per_visit <- maint_cost_per_visit_pct_zz*costo_activo_zz
  seguro_start <- grace_period + 1
  
  retail_price <- costo_activo_zz*(1+markup_zz)
  down_payment_amt <-  retail_price*down_payment_pct_zz
  principal <- retail_price*(1-down_payment_pct_zz)
  monthly_rate <- ann_rate_zz/12
  
  seguro_cost_est <- costo_activo_zz*seguro_est_pct_zz ## Seguro 
  op_de_comp <- retail_price*op_de_comp_est_pct_zz
  
  
  
  finance_table <- amort_time_form('2000-01-01',principal,ann_rate_zz,loan_term_zz,grace_period_zz)  
  
  df <- finance_table %>%
    mutate(
      enganche = ifelse(month == 0, enganche_zz, 0)
      , legal_fees = ifelse(month == 0, legal_fees_zz, 0)
      , op_de_comp = ifelse(month== loan_term_zz, op_de_comp,0)
      
      , cost_seguro = ifelse((12-seguro_start+month) %% 12 != 0,0 
                             , ifelse(month>loan_term_zz,0
                                      , seguro_cost_est*seguro_defl_rate_zz^(floor(month/12))
                             ))
      
      , cost_maint = ifelse(month <= 24,0  ## Doesn't cost anything for first 2 years
                            ,ifelse(month> loan_term_zz, 0
                                    ,ifelse(month %% 12 != 0, 0
                                            ,maint_cost_per_visit*(1+maint_infl_zz)^(pmax(floor(month / 12 - 3), 0))
                                    )))
      , other_costs = ifelse(month == 0, costs_zz, 0)
    )
  
  # Calculate the maintenence and insurance payments
  total_main_cost <- sum(df$cost_maint)*(1+maint_premium_zz)
  maint_pymnt <-  total_main_cost/(loan_term_zz-seguro_start+1)
  total_seguro_cost <- sum(df$cost_seguro)
  seguro_pymnt <-  total_seguro_cost/(loan_term_zz-seguro_start+1)
  
  df <- df |> 
    mutate(
      , seguro_pymnt = ifelse(month >= seguro_start & month <= loan_term_zz, seguro_pymnt,0)
      , maint_pymnt = ifelse(month >= seguro_start & month <= loan_term_zz, maint_pymnt,0)
      , income_lease = payment + enganche + op_de_comp
      , income_wservicios = income_lease + seguro_pymnt + legal_fees + maint_pymnt
      #, total_monthly_payment = payment + seguro + legal_fees + enganche + op_de_comp
      , iva = income_wservicios*iva_rate_zz
      , income_total = income_wservicios + iva
      , capital_costs =
        ifelse(month==0,costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m1,
               ifelse(month==1,costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m2,
                      ifelse(month==2,costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m3
                             ,0)))
      , debt_balance = ifelse(month==0, costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m1 + other_costs -( payment + enganche + op_de_comp),NA)
    ) 
  
  # calculate debt cost
  for(i in 2:loan_term_zz){
    df$debt_balance[i] = (df$debt_balance[i-1] + df$capital_costs[i]  - df$income_lease[i])*(1+albedo_wacc_zz/12) # Taking lease income rather than income_wservicios
  }
  
  df <- df |>
    mutate(
      lag_db = lag(debt_balance,1),
      , debt_cost = pmax(lag_db*(albedo_wacc_zz/12),0)
      , debt_cost = ifelse(month==0,0,debt_cost)
    ) |>
    select(-c(lag_db))
  
  # calculate inflows and out-flows
  df <- df |>
    mutate(
      , expense_lease = capital_costs + other_costs
      , expense_lease_wdebt = expense_lease  +  debt_cost
      , expense_wservicios = expense_lease_wdebt + cost_maint + cost_seguro
      , expense_total = expense_wservicios + iva  # currently IVA is in and out 
      
      , nii_lease = income_lease - expense_lease
      , nii_lease_wdebt = income_lease - expense_lease_wdebt
      , nii_wservicios = income_wservicios - expense_wservicios
      , nii_total = income_total - expense_total
      
      , cum_nii_lease = cumsum(nii_lease)
      , cum_nii_lease_wdebt = cumsum(nii_lease_wdebt)
      , cum_nii_wservicios = cumsum(nii_wservicios)
      , cum_nii_total = cumsum(nii_total)
      
      # this makes things easier for duration calc
      , pos_nii_lease_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_lease<0,9999,month)
      , pos_nii_lease_wdebt_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_lease_wdebt<0,9999,month)
      , pos_nii_wservicios_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_wservicios<0,9999,month)
      , pos_nii_total_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_total<0,9999,month)
    )
  
  # NPV
  df <- df |>
    mutate(
      discount_fact = 1/(1+ (risk_free_rate_zz/12))^month
      , npv_nii_lease = discount_fact*nii_lease
      , npv_nii_lease_wdebt = discount_fact*nii_lease_wdebt
      , npv_nii_wservicios = discount_fact*nii_wservicios
      , npv_nii_total = discount_fact*nii_total
    )
  
  
  return(df)
}


get_kpis <- function(nii_tab) {
  
  names <- c("Leasing", "Leasing w Debt", "w Servicios", "Total w IVA")
  income <- c(sum(nii_tab$income_lease), sum(nii_tab$income_lease), sum(nii_tab$income_wservicios), sum(nii_tab$income_total))
  expense <- c(sum(nii_tab$expense_lease), sum(nii_tab$expense_lease_wdebt), sum(nii_tab$expense_wservicios), sum(nii_tab$expense_total))
  profit <- income-expense
  npv <- c(sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_lease), sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_lease_wdebt), sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_wservicios), sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_total))
  irr <- c(round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_lease)*12*100,1), round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_lease_wdebt)*12*100,1), round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_wservicios)*12*100,1), round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_total)*12*100,1))
  gross_margin <- (profit/expense)*100
  payback_period <- c(min(nii_tab$pos_nii_lease_mon), min(nii_tab$pos_nii_lease_wdebt_mon), min(nii_tab$pos_nii_wservicios_mon), min(nii_tab$pos_nii_total_mon))
  
  KPI_table <- rbind(
    income <- income
    , expense <- expense
    , profit <- income-expense
    , npv <- npv
    , irr <- irr
    , gross_margin <- gross_margin
    , payback_period <- payback_period
  )
  
  kpis <- c("Income", "Expense", "Profit", "Net Present Value", "IRR", "Gross Margin", "Payback Period")
  KPI_table <- as.data.frame(KPI_table) |> mutate_if(is.numeric,round, 1)
  KPI_table <- cbind(kpis, KPI_table)
  
  
  names(KPI_table) <-  c("KPI", "Leasing", "Leasing w Debt", "w Servicios", "Total w IVA")
  KPI_table
  
}


# Global Options ----
iva_rate <- 0.12
albedo_wacc <- 0.09
risk_free_rate <- 0.04
seguro_defl_rate <- 0.96
seguro_est_pct <- 0.017
op_de_comp_est_pct <- 0.01
commission_cost_est <- 0.023

maint_cost_per_visit_est_pct <- 0.028
maint_inflation_rate_pct <- 0.05

# Timing for cost de activo --- not sure if this is constant across all loans?
activo_expense_m1 <- 0.5
activo_expense_m2 <- 0.4
activo_expense_m3 <- 0.1

# Loan Info  / Client Options ----
costo_activo <- 38032
down_payment_pct <- 0.03
term_months <- 63
grace_period <- 3 
legal_fees <- 0


# Pricing Strat 
markup <- 0.0309

#

# principal <- retail_price*(1-down_payment_pct)
#

# 
other_costs <- costo_activo*commission_cost_est ## Commission Cost 
# 
# seguro_cost_est <- costo_activo*seguro_est_pct ## Seguro 
# op_de_comp <- retail_price*op_de_comp_est_pct




nii_tab <- nii_table_fun(
  ann_rate_zz = ann_rate
  , grace_period_zz = grace_period
  , markup_zz = markup
  , down_payment_pct_zz = down_payment_pct
  , enganche_zz = down_payment_amt
  , legal_fees_zz = legal_fees
  , op_de_comp_est_pct_zz = op_de_comp_est_pct
  , seguro_est_pct_zz = seguro_est_pct
  , loan_term_zz = term_months
  , iva_rate_zz = iva_rate
  , costo_activo_zz = costo_activo
  , costs_zz = other_costs
  , albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc
  , risk_free_rate_zz = risk_free_rate

  , maint_infl_zz = maint_inflation_rate_pct
  , maint_premium_zz = maint_premium
  , seguro_defl_rate_zz = seguro_defl_rate
  
)

  seguro_cost_est <- costo_activo_zz*seguro_est_pct_zz ## Seguro 
  op_de_comp <- retail_price*op_de_comp_est_pct_zz
  
  
  
  finance_table <- amort_time_form('2000-01-01',principal,ann_rate_zz,loan_term_zz,grace_period_zz)  
  
  df <- finance_table %>%
    mutate(
      enganche = ifelse(month == 0, enganche_zz, 0)
      , legal_fees = ifelse(month == 0, legal_fees_zz, 0)
      , op_de_comp = ifelse(month== loan_term_zz, op_de_comp,0)
      
      , cost_seguro = ifelse((12-seguro_start+month) %% 12 != 0,0 
                             , ifelse(month>loan_term_zz,0
                                      , seguro_cost_est*seguro_defl_rate_zz^(floor(month/12))
                             ))
      
      , cost_maint = ifelse(month <= 24,0  ## Doesn't cost anything for first 2 years
                            ,ifelse(month> loan_term_zz, 0
                                    ,ifelse(month %% 12 != 0, 0
                                            ,maint_cost_per_visit*(1+maint_infl_zz)^(pmax(floor(month / 12 - 3), 0))
                                    )))
      , other_costs = ifelse(month == 0, costs_zz, 0)
    )
  
  # Calculate the maintenence and insurance payments
  total_main_cost <- sum(df$cost_maint)*(1+maint_premium_zz)
  maint_pymnt <-  total_main_cost/(loan_term_zz-seguro_start+1)
  total_seguro_cost <- sum(df$cost_seguro)
  seguro_pymnt <-  total_seguro_cost/(loan_term_zz-seguro_start+1)
  
  df <- df |> 
    mutate(
      , seguro_pymnt = ifelse(month >= seguro_start & month <= loan_term_zz, seguro_pymnt,0)
      , maint_pymnt = ifelse(month >= seguro_start & month <= loan_term_zz, maint_pymnt,0)
      , income_lease = payment + enganche + op_de_comp
      , income_wservicios = income_lease + seguro_pymnt + legal_fees + maint_pymnt
      #, total_monthly_payment = payment + seguro + legal_fees + enganche + op_de_comp
      , iva = income_wservicios*iva_rate_zz
      , income_total = income_wservicios + iva
      , capital_costs =
        ifelse(month==0,costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m1,
               ifelse(month==1,costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m2,
                      ifelse(month==2,costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m3
                             ,0)))
      , debt_balance = ifelse(month==0, costo_activo_zz*activo_expense_m1 + other_costs -( payment + enganche + op_de_comp),NA)
    ) 
  
  # calculate debt cost
  for(i in 2:loan_term_zz){
    df$debt_balance[i] = (df$debt_balance[i-1] + df$capital_costs[i]  - df$income_lease[i])*(1+albedo_wacc_zz/12) # Taking lease income rather than income_wservicios
  }
  
  df <- df |>
    mutate(
      lag_db = lag(debt_balance,1),
      , debt_cost = pmax(lag_db*(albedo_wacc_zz/12),0)
      , debt_cost = ifelse(month==0,0,debt_cost)
    ) |>
    select(-c(lag_db))
  
  # calculate inflows and out-flows
  df <- df |>
    mutate(
      , expense_lease = capital_costs + other_costs
      , expense_lease_wdebt = expense_lease  +  debt_cost
      , expense_wservicios = expense_lease_wdebt + cost_maint + cost_seguro
      , expense_total = expense_wservicios + iva  # currently IVA is in and out 
      
      , nii_lease = income_lease - expense_lease
      , nii_lease_wdebt = income_lease - expense_lease_wdebt
      , nii_wservicios = income_wservicios - expense_wservicios
      , nii_total = income_total - expense_total
      
      , cum_nii_lease = cumsum(nii_lease)
      , cum_nii_lease_wdebt = cumsum(nii_lease_wdebt)
      , cum_nii_wservicios = cumsum(nii_wservicios)
      , cum_nii_total = cumsum(nii_total)
      
      # this makes things easier for duration calc
      , pos_nii_lease_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_lease<0,9999,month)
      , pos_nii_lease_wdebt_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_lease_wdebt<0,9999,month)
      , pos_nii_wservicios_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_wservicios<0,9999,month)
      , pos_nii_total_mon = ifelse(cum_nii_total<0,9999,month)
    )
  
  # NPV
  df <- df |>
    mutate(
      discount_fact = 1/(1+ (risk_free_rate_zz/12))^month
      , npv_nii_lease = discount_fact*nii_lease
      , npv_nii_lease_wdebt = discount_fact*nii_lease_wdebt
      , npv_nii_wservicios = discount_fact*nii_wservicios
      , npv_nii_total = discount_fact*nii_total
    )
  
  
  return(df)
}


get_kpis <- function(nii_tab) {
  
  names <- c("Leasing", "Leasing w Debt", "w Servicios", "Total w IVA")
  income <- c(sum(nii_tab$income_lease), sum(nii_tab$income_lease), sum(nii_tab$income_wservicios), sum(nii_tab$income_total))
  expense <- c(sum(nii_tab$expense_lease), sum(nii_tab$expense_lease_wdebt), sum(nii_tab$expense_wservicios), sum(nii_tab$expense_total))
  profit <- income-expense
  npv <- c(sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_lease), sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_lease_wdebt), sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_wservicios), sum(nii_tab$npv_nii_total))
  irr <- c(round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_lease)*12*100,1), round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_lease_wdebt)*12*100,1), round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_wservicios)*12*100,1), round(jrvFinance::irr(nii_tab$nii_total)*12*100,1))
  gross_margin <- (profit/expense)*100
  payback_period <- c(min(nii_tab$pos_nii_lease_mon), min(nii_tab$pos_nii_lease_wdebt_mon), min(nii_tab$pos_nii_wservicios_mon), min(nii_tab$pos_nii_total_mon))
  
  KPI_table <- rbind(
    income <- income
    , expense <- expense
    , profit <- income-expense
    , npv <- npv
    , irr <- irr
    , gross_margin <- gross_margin
    , payback_period <- payback_period
  )
  
  kpis <- c("Income", "Expense", "Profit", "Net Present Value", "IRR", "Gross Margin", "Payback Period")
  KPI_table <- as.data.frame(KPI_table) |> mutate_if(is.numeric,round, 1)
  KPI_table <- cbind(kpis, KPI_table)
  
  
  names(KPI_table) <-  c("KPI", "Leasing", "Leasing w Debt", "w Servicios", "Total w IVA")
  KPI_table
  
}


# Global Options ----
iva_rate <- 0.12
albedo_wacc <- 0.09
risk_free_rate <- 0.04
seguro_defl_rate <- 0.96
seguro_est_pct <- 0.017
op_de_comp_est_pct <- 0.01
commission_cost_est <- 0.023

maint_cost_per_visit_est_pct <- 0.028
maint_inflation_rate_pct <- 0.05

# Timing for cost de activo --- not sure if this is constant across all loans?
activo_expense_m1 <- 0.5
activo_expense_m2 <- 0.4
activo_expense_m3 <- 0.1

# Loan Info  / Client Options ----
costo_activo <- 38032
down_payment_pct <- 0.03
term_months <- 63
grace_period <- 3 
legal_fees <- 0


# Pricing Strat 
markup <- 0.0309
ann_rate <- 0.182
maint_premium <- 0.1

# 
# # Calculated 
# retail_price <- costo_activo*(1+markup)
# down_payment_amt <-  retail_price*down_payment_pct
# principal <- retail_price*(1-down_payment_pct)
# 
# monthly_rate <- ann_rate/12
# 
other_costs <- costo_activo*commission_cost_est ## Commission Cost 
# 
# seguro_cost_est <- costo_activo*seguro_est_pct ## Seguro 
# op_de_comp <- retail_price*op_de_comp_est_pct




nii_tab <- nii_table_fun(
  ann_rate_zz = ann_rate
  , grace_period_zz = grace_period
  , markup_zz = markup
  , down_payment_pct_zz = down_payment_pct
  , enganche_zz = down_payment_amt
  , legal_fees_zz = legal_fees
  , op_de_comp_est_pct_zz = op_de_comp_est_pct
  , seguro_est_pct_zz = seguro_est_pct
  , loan_term_zz = term_months
  , iva_rate_zz = iva_rate
  , costo_activo_zz = costo_activo
  , costs_zz = other_costs
  , albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc
  , risk_free_rate_zz = risk_free_rate
  , maint_cost_per_visit_pct_zz = maint_cost_per_visit_est_pct
  , maint_infl_zz = maint_inflation_rate_pct
  , maint_premium_zz = maint_premium
  , seguro_defl_rate_zz = seguro_defl_rate
  
)

content:
library(shiny)
library(dplyr)
library(jrvFinance)
library(reactable)

# Source your functions (assuming they're saved in 'loan_kpi_functions.R')
source("R/calculate_kpis.R")

ui <- fluidPage(
  titlePanel("Loan KPI Calculator"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      numericInput("costo_activo", "Asset Cost", value = 38032),
      numericInput("markup", "Markup (%)", value = 0.0309),
      numericInput("down_payment_pct", "Down Payment (%)", value = 0.03),
      numericInput("term_months", "Loan Term (months)", value = 63),
      numericInput("grace_period", "Grace Period (months)", value = 3),
      numericInput("ann_rate", "Annual Interest Rate (%)", value = 0.182),
      numericInput("legal_fees", "Legal Fees", value = 0),
      numericInput("maint_premium", "Maintenance Premium (%)", value = 0.1),
      actionButton("calc_btn", "Calculate KPIs")
    ),
    
    mainPanel(
      h3("KPI Table"),
      tableOutput("kpi_table"),
      hr(),
      h3("Amortization Summary by Year"),
      reactableOutput("amort_table")
    )
    
  )
)

server <- function(input, output) {
  observeEvent(input$calc_btn, {
    retail_price <- input$costo_activo * (1 + input$markup)
    down_payment_amt <- retail_price * input$down_payment_pct
    other_costs <- input$costo_activo * commission_cost_est
    
    
    
      partial_table <- calculate_cashflows_fun(
        ann_rate_zz = input$ann_rate,
        grace_period_zz = input$grace_period,
        markup_zz = input$markup,
        down_payment_pct_zz = input$down_payment_pct,
        #enganche_zz = down_payment_amt,
        legal_fees_zz = input$legal_fees,
        op_de_comp_est_pct_zz = op_de_comp_est_pct,
        seguro_est_pct_zz = seguro_est_pct,
        loan_term_zz = input$term_months,
        area_zz = 'Guatemala', 
        costo_activo_zz = input$costo_activo,
        costs_zz = other_costs,
        albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc,
        risk_free_rate_zz = risk_free_rate,
        maint_cost_per_visit_pct_zz = maint_cost_per_visit_est_pct,
        maint_infl_zz = maint_inflation_rate_pct,
        maint_premium_zz = input$maint_premium,
        seguro_defl_rate_zz = seguro_defl_rate
    )
      
      cash_flow_data <- calculate_inc_exp_fun(partial_table,
                          loan_term_zz = input$term_months
                          , grace_period_zz = input$grace_period,
                          risk_free_rate_zz=risk_free_rate , albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc)
    
  
    output$kpi_table <- renderTable({
      get_kpis(cash_flow_data)
    })
    
    amort_summary <- cash_flow_data  %>%
      mutate(
        year = floor(month / 12) + 1,
        total_income = income_total,
        total_expense = expense_total
      ) %>%
      select(year, month, payment, total_income, total_expense) |>
      mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 1)
    
    
    output$amort_ui <- renderUI({
      years <- unique(amort_summary$year)
      lapply(years, function(y) {
        wellPanel(
          h4(paste("Year", y)),
          tableOutput(paste0("amort_year_", y))
        )
      })
    })
    
    # Dynamically render each year's table
    output$amort_table <- renderReactable({
      reactable(amort_summary
                , pagination = TRUE
                , groupBy = "year"
      )
  })
    
  })
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)

                 , dbname = "postgres"

                 , port = 5432

# first set global variables: -------------------------------------------------

# Global Options

maint_cost_per_visit_est_pct <- 0.028
maint_inflation_rate_pct <- 0.05

# Timing for cost de activo --- not sure if this is constant across all loans?

# Loan Info  / Client Options

down_payment_pct <- 0.00
term_months <- 51

# Pricing Strat

ann_rate <- 0.2040863
maint_premium <- 0.1
target_margin <- 0.05


# Next pull data from db2 ------------------------------------
nii_from_db2 <- dbGetQuery(con, sql("
WITH project_dat AS (
  SELECT   
      id 
      , project_reference 
      , client_name
      , project_cost_partner_contract_currency
      , partner_contract_currency
      , CASE 
          WHEN project_currency = 'GTQ' AND partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN project_cost_partner_contract_currency*7.8

          WHEN project_currency = 'USD' AND partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN project_cost_partner_contract_currency
          END AS costo_activo
      , retail_price_project_currency
      , project_currency
      , duration
      , grace_period
      , monthly_interest_rate_percent/100 AS monthly_rate
      , monthly_interest_rate_percent*12/100 AS annual_rate
      , country_name
  FROM app.mv_projects_v1

  WHERE 1=1
  AND sale_type = 'Financiado'
)

, mcf AS (
    SELECT  
     project_id, quote_id
     , payment_number-1 AS month
     , remaining_principal_project_currency as ending_principal
     , down_payment_project_currency AS enganche
     , legal_costs_project_currency AS legal_fees
     , asset_transfer_value_project_currency AS op_de_comp
     , insurance_payment_project_currency AS seguro_pymnt
     , insurance_cost_project_currency AS cost_seguro
      , maintenance_cost_project_currency AS cost_maint
     , COALESCE(maintenance_payment_project_currency,0 ) AS maint_pymnt
     , interest_payment_project_currency AS interest_accrued
     , monthly_payment_project_currency AS payment
     , commission_cost_project_currency AS other_costs 
    
    FROM monthly_cash_flows
    --WHERE project_id = 1576
)

, das_join AS (
  SELECT p.*, mcf.*
  FROM project_dat p 
  LEFT JOIN mcf
  ON p.id = mcf.project_id 
)

SELECT * FROM das_join  
WHERE 1=1
AND project_reference = '1885-03'
"))

# Next Calculate cashflows based on global inputs -------------------------------------
## this should basically match the table nii_from_db2 but with fewer columns
source('R/split_amortization.R')
source('R/amortization_functions.R')
source('R/pricing_functions.R')
pricing_info_table <- fromJSON("./pricing_info.json")

partial_table <- calculate_cashflows_fun(
  ann_rate_zz = ann_rate
  , grace_period_zz = grace_period
  , markup_zz = markup
  , down_payment_pct_zz = down_payment_pct
  , legal_fees_zz = legal_fees
  , op_de_comp_est_pct_zz = op_de_comp_est_pct
  , seguro_est_pct_zz = seguro_est_pct
  , loan_term_zz = term_months
  , area_zz = 'GT'
  , costo_activo_zz = costo_activo
  , costs_zz = commission_cost_est
  , albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc
  , risk_free_rate_zz = risk_free_rate
  , maint_cost_per_visit_pct_zz = maint_cost_per_visit_est_pct
  , maint_infl_zz = maint_inflation_rate_pct
  , maint_premium_zz = maint_premium
  , seguro_defl_rate_zz = seguro_defl_rate
)

# Calculate the income and expenses -----------------------------------
inc_exp_from_calc <- calculate_inc_exp_fun(partial_table, term_months, grace_period_zz = grace_period,risk_free_rate_zz=risk_free_rate , albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc)
inc_exp_from_db2 <- calculate_inc_exp_fun(nii_from_db2, term_months, grace_period_zz = grace_period,risk_free_rate_zz=risk_free_rate , albedo_wacc_zz = albedo_wacc )

write.csv(inc_exp_from_calc, "dev/inc_exp_from_calc.csv")

# Calculate KPIs 
source('R/calculate_kpis.R')

kpi_table <- get_kpis(inc_exp_from_db2)
kpi_table

name: dev/geography_table_testing.sql
content:
/* Get the project data */ 
WITH project_dat AS (
  SELECT  
    id 
    , project_reference 
    , client_name
    , project_date
    , project_cost_partner_contract_currency, partner_contract_currency
    , country_name, country_id
    , department_name, department_id
    , municipality_name, municipality_id, rural_area
    , provider_id, provider_name
    , installed_potential_kw
    , retail_price_project_currency, total_legal_costs_project_currency, project_currency
    
FROM app.mv_projects_v1

  WHERE 1=1
  AND sale_type = 'Financiado'
)

/* Get the cashflow data  */ 
, mcf AS (
    SELECT  
     project_id, quote_id
     , SUM(legal_costs_project_currency) AS legal_fees
     , SUM(asset_transfer_value_project_currency) AS op_de_comp
     --, MAX(insurance_payment_project_currency) AS seguro_pymnt
     , MAX(
          CASE 
            WHEN insurance_cost_project_currency=0 THEN NULL 
            --WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN insurance_cost_project_currency*7.8
            ELSE insurance_cost_project_currency 
          END
        ) AS insurance_cost_project_currency
     , MIN(
        CASE 
          WHEN maintenance_cost_project_currency =0 THEN NULL 
          --WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN maintenance_cost_project_currency*7.8
          ELSE maintenance_cost_project_currency 
        END
      ) AS maintenance_cost_project_currency
    
    FROM monthly_cash_flows
    GROUP BY project_id, quote_id
)

/* join project and cash flow  */ 
, das_join AS (
  SELECT p.*, mcf.*
  FROM project_dat p 
  LEFT JOIN mcf
  ON p.id = mcf.project_id 
)

/* convert currencies -- need more information for other currencies */ 
, var_create AS (
  SELECT *
    , CASE 
        WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN insurance_cost_project_currency*7.8
        ELSE insurance_cost_project_currency 
      END  AS insurance_cost_gtq
    , CASE 
        WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN maintenance_cost_project_currency*7.8
        ELSE maintenance_cost_project_currency 
      END AS maintenance_cost_gtq
      
    , CASE 
        WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN retail_price_project_currency*7.8
        ELSE retail_price_project_currency 
      END AS retail_price_gtq
      
    , CASE 
        WHEN partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN project_cost_partner_contract_currency*7.8
        ELSE project_cost_partner_contract_currency 
      END AS project_cost_partner_gtq
  FROM das_join
) 

, var_create2 AS (
  SELECT *
    , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq/retail_price_project_currency)*100 END AS seguro_pct_cost
    , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq/retail_price_project_currency)*100 END AS maint_pct_cost
    , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq/installed_potential_kw)*100 END AS seguro_pct_kw
    , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq/installed_potential_kw)*100 END AS maint_pct_kw
  FROM var_create
) 


/* Aggregate data - the following are examples but in the end I think we basically want a waterfall logic, that takes as much information as possible and creates an estimate based on that */ 


, by_area_provider AS (
    SELECT 
      country_name, department_name, municipality_name, provider_name
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_insurance
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_maintenance
        
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE insurance_cost_gtq END) AS insurance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE maintenance_cost_gtq END) AS maintenance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_maint
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_maint
    
    FROM var_create2
    GROUP BY country_name, department_name, municipality_name, provider_name
)

, by_country AS (
    SELECT 
      country_name
      , 'ANY' AS department_name
      , 'ANY' AS municipality_name
      , 'ANY' AS provider_name
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_insurance
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_maintenance
        
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE insurance_cost_gtq END) AS insurance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE maintenance_cost_gtq END) AS maintenance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_maint
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_maint
    
    FROM var_create
    GROUP BY country_name
)

, all_data_tab AS (
  SELECT * FROM by_country
  UNION 
  SELECT * FROM by_area_provider
)

SELECT country_name, department_name, municipality_name, provider_name
  , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw_insur IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN installed_potential_kw_insur = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq_winst/installed_potential_kw_insur)*100 END AS avg_insurance_cost_pkw
  , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw_maint IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN installed_potential_kw_maint = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq_winst/installed_potential_kw_maint)*100 END AS avg_maintenance_cost_pkw
  , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_insur IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_insur = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq_winst/project_cost_partner_gtq_insur)*100 END AS avg_insurance_cost_pcost
  , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_maint IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_maint = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq_winst/project_cost_partner_gtq_maint)*100 END AS avg_maintenance_cost_pcost
FROM all_data_tab

name: dev/geography_testing.Rmd
content:
---
title: "Geography Table"
output: html_document
date: "2025-11-24"
---


```{r setup, include=FALSE}
knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)


library(DBI)
library(RPostgres)
library(RPostgreSQL)
library(connections)
library(odbc)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(lubridate)
library(plotly)

# Set your default connection - or specify in each chunck
knitr::opts_chunk$set(connection = "con")


```

# Connect 

```{r}
readRenviron("C://USERS//imcgr//.Renviron")
my_password <- Sys.getenv("SUPABASE_PASWWORD")
# 
 drv <- dbDriver("PostgreSQL")
 
 # Set connection
  con <- dbConnect(drv
                   , dbname = "postgres"
                   , host = "db.ghulhjlbniwczcmhrysy.supabase.co"
                   , port = 5432
                   , user = "postgres"
                   , password =  my_password
                   )

    con_pane <- connections::connection_open(drv
      , dbname = "postgres"
      , host = "db.ghulhjlbniwczcmhrysy.supabase.co"
      , port = 5432
      , user = "postgres"
      , password =  my_password
    )
```

# Questions

- Right now it seams like things are mostly coded off of retail price. In some ways this makes sense for insurance but idk about maintenance? 
- The table should have a unique row for each (country_id, department_id, municipality_id, providor_id,  maybe year??) and will have the tax_rate, maintenence_rate, and insurance_rate. I've started to set this up in the SQL in the attached query (feel free to ignore). But as for the logic I think what I really want is to have a sort of waterfall. If the full location and provider are given, take the average of the location and provider. If only the location is known then take the average of the location by as much granularity as possible (i.e. if the municipality is known use the average of that if only the country use that). 

- these aren't real costs so we should get them. 
- urban, highland, rural segment?
- does it depend on equipment or other things?

# Data work 

```{sql, output.var = 'test_geo_tab'}
--, output.var = 'geography_tab_test'}

/* Get the project data */ 
WITH project_dat AS (
  SELECT  
    id 
    , project_reference 
    , client_name
    , project_date
    , project_cost_partner_contract_currency, partner_contract_currency
    , country_name, country_id
    , department_name, department_id
    , municipality_name, municipality_id, rural_area
    , provider_id, provider_name
    , installed_potential_kw
    , retail_price_project_currency, total_legal_costs_project_currency, project_currency
    
FROM app.mv_projects_v1

  WHERE 1=1
  AND sale_type = 'Financiado'
)

/* Get the cashflow data  */ 
, mcf AS (
    SELECT  
     project_id, quote_id
     , SUM(legal_costs_project_currency) AS legal_fees
     , SUM(asset_transfer_value_project_currency) AS op_de_comp
     --, MAX(insurance_payment_project_currency) AS seguro_pymnt
     , MAX(
          CASE 
            WHEN insurance_cost_project_currency=0 THEN NULL 
            --WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN insurance_cost_project_currency*7.8
            ELSE insurance_cost_project_currency 
          END
        ) AS insurance_cost_project_currency
     , MIN(
        CASE 
          WHEN maintenance_cost_project_currency =0 THEN NULL 
          --WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN maintenance_cost_project_currency*7.8
          ELSE maintenance_cost_project_currency 
        END
      ) AS maintenance_cost_project_currency
    
    FROM monthly_cash_flows
    GROUP BY project_id, quote_id
)

/* join project and cash flow  */ 
, das_join AS (
  SELECT p.*, mcf.*
  FROM project_dat p 
  LEFT JOIN mcf
  ON p.id = mcf.project_id 
)

/* convert currencies -- need more information for other currencies */ 
, var_create AS (
  SELECT *
    , CASE 
        WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN insurance_cost_project_currency*7.8
        ELSE insurance_cost_project_currency 
      END  AS insurance_cost_gtq
    , CASE 
        WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN maintenance_cost_project_currency*7.8
        ELSE maintenance_cost_project_currency 
      END AS maintenance_cost_gtq
      
    , CASE 
        WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN retail_price_project_currency*7.8
        ELSE retail_price_project_currency 
      END AS retail_price_gtq
      
    , CASE 
        WHEN partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN project_cost_partner_contract_currency*7.8
        ELSE project_cost_partner_contract_currency 
      END AS project_cost_partner_gtq
  FROM das_join
) 

, var_create2 AS (
  SELECT *
    , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq/retail_price_project_currency)*100 END AS seguro_pct_cost
    , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq/retail_price_project_currency)*100 END AS maint_pct_cost
    , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq/installed_potential_kw)*100 END AS seguro_pct_kw
    , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq/installed_potential_kw)*100 END AS maint_pct_kw
  FROM var_create
) 

/* Aggregate data - the following are examples but in the end I think we basically want a waterfall logic, that takes as much information as possible and creates an estimate based on that */ 
, by_area_provider AS (
    SELECT 
      country_name, department_name, municipality_name, provider_name
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_insurance
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_maintenance
        
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE insurance_cost_gtq END) AS insurance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE maintenance_cost_gtq END) AS maintenance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_maint
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_maint
    
    FROM var_create2
    GROUP BY country_name, department_name, municipality_name, provider_name
)

, by_country AS (
    SELECT 
      country_name
      , 'ANY' AS department_name
      , 'ANY' AS municipality_name
      , 'ANY' AS provider_name
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_insurance
      , SUM(CASE 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 
              WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0
              WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0
              ELSE  1
            END
          ) AS has_maintenance
        
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE insurance_cost_gtq END) AS insurance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw = 0 THEN 0 ELSE maintenance_cost_gtq END) AS maintenance_cost_gtq_winst 
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE installed_potential_kw END) AS installed_potential_kw_maint
      , SUM(CASE WHEN insurance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN insurance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_insur
      , SUM(CASE WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq = 0 THEN 0 WHEN maintenance_cost_gtq IS NULL THEN 0 ELSE project_cost_partner_gtq END) AS project_cost_partner_gtq_maint
    
    FROM var_create
    GROUP BY country_name
)

, all_data_tab AS (
  SELECT * FROM by_country
  UNION 
  SELECT * FROM by_area_provider
)

SELECT * FROM var_create2  /* FOR test_geo_tab*/

/*
SELECT * 
  , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw_insur IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN installed_potential_kw_insur = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq_winst/installed_potential_kw_insur)*100 END AS avg_insurance_cost_pkw
  , CASE WHEN installed_potential_kw_maint IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN installed_potential_kw_maint = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq_winst/installed_potential_kw_maint)*100 END AS avg_maintenance_cost_pkw
  , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_insur IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_insur = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (insurance_cost_gtq_winst/project_cost_partner_gtq_insur)*100 END AS avg_insurance_cost_pcost
  , CASE WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_maint IS NULL THEN NULL WHEN project_cost_partner_gtq_maint = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (maintenance_cost_gtq_winst/project_cost_partner_gtq_maint)*100 END AS avg_maintenance_cost_pcost
FROM all_data_tab
*/

```

```{r}
test_geo_tab |> arrange(installed_potential_kw) |> 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 2)
```

```{r}
plot_ly(type='scatter') |>
  add_trace(data=test_geo_tab, y=~retail_price_project_currency, x=~total_legal_costs_project_currency, color=~as.factor(project_currency))
```


```{r}
a <- test_geo_tab  |>
  mutate(
      seguro_pct_retail =  (insurance_cost_gtq/retail_price_project_currency)*100
    , maint_pct_retail = (maintenance_cost_gtq/retail_price_project_currency)*100
    , seguro_pct_kw =  (insurance_cost_gtq/installed_potential_kw)*100
    , cost_pct_kw = (project_cost_partner_gtq/installed_potential_kw)
  ) |>
  mutate_if(is.numeric,round, 2) 


by_provider <- a |>
  group_by(provider_name, country_name) |>
  summarize(
    count = n()
    , segu_avg = mean(seguro_pct_cost, na.rm=TRUE)
    , segu_min = min(seguro_pct_cost, na.rm=TRUE)
    , segu_max = max(seguro_pct_cost, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_avg = mean(maint_pct_cost, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_min = min(maint_pct_cost, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_max = max(maint_pct_cost, na.rm=TRUE)
  ) |> 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 4) 



by_area_provider <- a |>
  group_by(country_name, department_name, municipality_name, provider_name) |>
  summarize(
    count = n()
    , segu_avg = mean(seguro_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , segu_min = min(seguro_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , segu_max = max(seguro_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_avg = mean(maint_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_min = min(maint_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_max = max(maint_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
  ) |> 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 2) |>
  #filter(segu_avg == segu_min)
  arrange(country_name, desc(provider_name))


by_region <-  a |>
  group_by(country_name, department_name) |>
  summarize(
    count = n()
    , segu_avg = mean(seguro_pct_retail, na.rm=TRUE)
    , segu_min = min(seguro_pct_retail, na.rm=TRUE)
    , segu_max = max(seguro_pct_retail, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_avg = mean(maint_pct_retail, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_min = min(maint_pct_retail, na.rm=TRUE)
    , main_max = max(maint_pct_retail, na.rm=TRUE)
  ) |> 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 2) 
by_region


```



```{r}

plot_ly(type='scatter') |>
  add_trace(data=a, y=~retail_price_project_currency, x=~cost_maint, color=~as.factor(provider_name))

```

```{r}
geography_tab_test |>
  select(-c(has_insurance,has_maintenance, insurance_cost_gtq_winst, maintenance_cost_gtq_winst , installed_potential_kw_insur, installed_potential_kw_maint, project_cost_partner_gtq_insur, project_cost_partner_gtq_maint)) |>
  filter(!is.na(avg_insurance_cost_pkw))
```




# Install per kw

```{r}
a <- test_geo_tab |>
  mutate(
    is_rural = ifelse(rural_area == 'Yes',1,0),
    is_elsal = ifelse(country_name == 'El Salvador',1,0),
    is_hond = ifelse(country_name == 'Honduras',1,0),
    is_rural_kw = installed_potential_kw*is_rural,
    cost_pct_kw = (project_cost_partner_gtq/installed_potential_kw)
         ) |>
  filter(installed_potential_kw != 0) 


by_region <-  a |>
  group_by(country_name, department_name) |>
  summarize(
    count = n()
    , avg_cost_pct_kw = mean(cost_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , min_cost_pct_kw = min(cost_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , max_cost_pct_kw = max(cost_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
  ) |> 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 2) 
by_region


by_rural <-  a |>
  group_by(rural_area) |>
  summarize(
    count = n()
    , avg_cost_pct_kw = mean(cost_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , min_cost_pct_kw = min(cost_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
    , max_cost_pct_kw = max(cost_pct_kw, na.rm=TRUE)
  ) |> 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 2) 
by_rural


fit <- lm(project_cost_partner_gtq ~ installed_potential_kw + is_rural+is_rural_kw +is_elsal + is_hond, data=a)
summary(fit) 
```

WITH project_dat AS (

      , CASE 
          WHEN project_currency = 'GTQ' AND partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN project_cost_partner_contract_currency*7.8

          WHEN project_currency = 'USD' AND partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN project_cost_partner_contract_currency*7.8

  , project_id, quote_id
  , client_name

   , retail_price_project_currency
      , project_currency

      , (CASE WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN remaining_principal_project_currency*7.8 ELSE remaining_principal_project_currency END)  as ending_principal

      , maintenance_cost_project_currency AS cost_maint
     , COALESCE(maintenance_payment_project_currency,0 ) AS maint_pymnt
     , interest_payment_project_currency AS interest_accrued
     , monthly_payment_project_currency AS payment
     , commission_cost_project_currency AS other_costs 
    
    FROM monthly_cash_flows
    --WHERE project_id = 1576
)

, das_join AS (
  SELECT p.*, mcf.*
  FROM project_dat p 
  LEFT JOIN mcf
  ON p.id = mcf.project_id 
)

SELECT 
  COUNT(0) AS total 
  , SUM(CASE WHEN project_currency = 'GTQ' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS project_gtq
  , SUM(CASE WHEN partner_contract_currency = 'GTQ' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS contract_gtq
  , SUM(CASE WHEN partner_contract_currency = 'GTQ' AND project_currency = 'GTQ' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS both_gtq
  
  , SUM(CASE WHEN project_currency = 'USD' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS project_usd
  , SUM(CASE WHEN partner_contract_currency = 'USD' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS contract_usd
  , SUM(CASE WHEN partner_contract_currency = 'USD' AND project_currency = 'USD' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS both_usd
FROM das_join  
WHERE 1=1

AND  year >= 2025
--AND project_currency = 'GTQ'
--AND partner_contract_currency= 'GTQ'
--limit 100

---

output: html_document
date: "2025-12-08"

```{r setup, include=FALSE}


library(DBI)
library(RPostgres)
library(RPostgreSQL)
library(connections)
library(odbc)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(lubridate)
library(plotly)

# Set your default connection - or specify in each chunck
knitr::opts_chunk$set(connection = "con")

```


```{sql}
select * from monthly_cash_flows limit 100

```


```{sql connection=con}
WITH project_dat AS (
  SELECT   
      id 
      , project_reference 
      , client_name
      , project_cost_partner_contract_currency
      , partner_contract_currency
      , project_cost_gtq as costo_activo
      , retail_price_project_currency
      , project_currency
      , duration
      , grace_period
      , monthly_interest_rate_percent/100 AS monthly_rate
      , monthly_interest_rate_percent*12/100 AS annual_rate
      , country_name
      , EXTRACT(YEAR FROM project_date) AS year
  FROM app.mv_projects_v1

  WHERE 1=1
  AND sale_type = 'Financiado'
)

, mcf AS (
    SELECT  
     project_id, quote_id
     , payment_number-1 AS month
     , remaining_principal_project_currency as ending_principal
     , down_payment_gtq AS enganche
     , legal_costs_gtq AS legal_fees
     , asset_transfer_value_gtq AS op_de_comp
     , insurance_payment_gtq AS seguro_pymnt
          , insurance_cost_project_currency AS cost_seguro
         , maintenance_cost_project_currency AS cost_maint
     , COALESCE(maintenance_payment_gtq,0 ) AS maint_pymnt
     , interest_payment_gtq AS interest_accrued
     , monthly_payment_gtq AS payment
     
        , commission_cost_project_currency AS other_costs 
    
    FROM monthly_cash_flows
    --WHERE project_id = 1576
)

, das_join AS (
  SELECT p.*, mcf.*
  FROM project_dat p 
  LEFT JOIN mcf
  ON p.id = mcf.project_id 
)

SELECT * FROM das_join  
WHERE 1=1
--AND project_reference = '1885-03'
AND  year >= 2025
--AND project_currency = 'GTQ'
--AND partner_contract_currency= 'GTQ'
--limit 100

```


```{sql}
  select * from 
  analytics.int_monthly_cash_flows_gtq
  --where project_reference = '441-01'
  limit 100
```

```{sql}

WITH financed_monthly_cash_flows AS (
    select 
        mcf.*,
        p.project_reference,
        p.name AS project_name,
        q.first_payment_date,
        q.sale_type
    FROM analytics.int_static_monthly_cash_flows_convert_currencies mcf
    JOIN quotes q on mcf.quote_id = q.id
    JOIN estimates e on q.estimate_id = e.id
    JOIN projects p on e.project_id = p.id
    WHERE q.sale_type = 'Financiado'
    )
    
    select * 
    FROM financed_monthly_cash_flows
    where 1=1
    AND project_reference = '1868-01'


```


```{r}
nii_from_db2 |>
  filter(project_reference == '204-01')
```

library(shiny) library(shinydashboard) library(bslib) shinylive::export("C:/Users/imcgr/git/quoting_tool/AlbedoQuoteR", "C:/Users/imcgr/git/quoting_tool/test_app") source('./R/amortization_functions.R') source('./R/pricing_functions.R') source('./R/split_amortization.R') source('./R/calculate_kpis.R') projects <- read.csv("./data/projects_for_app.csv") ## see app_features.Rmd ui <- fluidPage( titlePanel("Quote Generator"), sidebarLayout( sidebarPanel( selectInput("project_select", "Choose a Project:", choices = projects$name, selected = NULL), # Sliders numericInput("costo_activo", "Asset Cost (sin IVA)", value = 115921), sliderInput("duration", "Duration (months):", min = 12, max = 126, value = 12, step = 1), sliderInput("interest_rate", "Interest Rate (%):", min = 10, max = 24, value = 10, step = 0.01), sliderInput("retail_price", "Retail Price:", min = 0, max = 100, value = 50, step = 1), sliderInput("grace_period", "Grace Period (months):", min = 0, max = 5, value = 0, step = 1), sliderInput("down_payment", "Down Payment (%):", min = 0, max = 1, value = 0, step = 0.01) ), mainPanel( layout_column_wrap( value_box( title = "Retail Price", value = uiOutput("retail_price_box"), color = 'green', showcase = icon("dollar-sign"), width = 4) , value_box( title = "Monthly Payment", value = uiOutput("monthly_payment_box"), color = 'orange', #showcase_layout = "middle center", showcase = icon("calendar"), full_screen = TRUE ), value_box( title = "IRR", value = uiOutput("irr_box"), color = 'blue', #showcase_layout = "top right", showcase = icon("leaf") ), width = 1/3 ), tabsetPanel( tabPanel("Client Characteristics", tableOutput("client_table")), tabPanel("Project Characteristics", tableOutput("project_table")), tabPanel("Cash Flow Table", tableOutput("cash_flow_table")), tabPanel("Profit Characteristics", tableOutput("kpi_table"), tableOutput("summary_table")), tabPanel("Global Inputs" , numericInput("op_de_comp_est_pct_zz", "Op de Comp Est %", value = 0.01, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) , numericInput("albedo_wacc_zz", "Albedo WACC", value = 0.10, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) , numericInput("risk_free_rate_zz", "Risk-Free Rate", value = 0.04, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) , numericInput("maint_infl_zz", "Maintenance Inflation", value = 0.05, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) , numericInput("maint_premium_ss", "Maintenance Premium", value = 0, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) , numericInput("seguro_defl_rate_zz", "Seguro Defl Rate", value = 0.96, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) , numericInput("legal_fees_ss", "Legal Fees", value = 2350, min = 0, max = 8000, step = 0.01) , numericInput("maint_cost_per_visit_pct_ss", "Maintenance Cost First Visit", value = 0.0385, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) # NOte need to fix to allow NAs , numericInput("seguro_est_pct_ss", "Seguro Cost First Visit", value = 0.01, min = 0, max = 1, step = 0.01) # NOte need to fix to allow NAs ) # End tab panel ) # end tabset panel ) # end main panel ) # end sidebar layout ) # end fluid page server <- function(input, output, session) { selected_project <- reactive({ req(input$project_select) projects[projects$name == input$project_select, ] }) # --- Update sliders when project changes --- observeEvent(selected_project(), { proj <- selected_project() # Duration updateSliderInput(session, "duration", value = proj$duration) # Interest Rate # Find the interest rate given the monthly payment starting_rate <- find_rate( principal_zz = proj$retail_price_project_currency - proj$down_payment_project_currency, payment_zz = proj$monthly_payment_project_currency, term_zz = (proj$duration - proj$grace_period)*-1 ) updateSliderInput(session, "interest_rate", value = starting_rate) project_cost_up <- reactive({ if(input$project_select == 'Test'){ input$costo_activo } else { proj$project_cost_partner_contract_currency } }) # Retail Price: +/- 10% range retail <- proj$retail_price_project_currency updateSliderInput(session, "retail_price", min = project_cost_up(), max = project_cost_up()*1.5, value = retail) # Grace Period updateSliderInput(session, "grace_period", value = proj$grace_period) }) project_cost_up <- reactive({ proj <- selected_project() if(input$project_select == 'Test'){ input$costo_activo } else { proj$project_cost_partner_contract_currency } }) cash_flow_data <- reactive({ proj <- selected_project() costo_activo <- project_cost_up() partial_table <- calculate_cashflows_fun( # User inputs ann_rate_zz = input$interest_rate/100 , grace_period_zz = input$grace_period , down_payment_pct_zz = input$down_payment , loan_term_zz = input$duration # Pulled from project , area_zz = proj$country_name , costo_activo_zz = costo_activo # calculated , markup_zz = (input$retail_price/costo_activo -1) , costs_zz = input$retail_price*0.03 , legal_fees_zz = input$legal_fees_ss , maint_cost_per_visit_pct_zz = input$maint_cost_per_visit_pct_ss , seguro_est_pct_zz = input$seguro_est_pct_ss # Global variables , op_de_comp_est_pct_zz = 0.01 , albedo_wacc_zz = 0.10 , risk_free_rate_zz = 0.04 , maint_infl_zz = 0.05 , maint_premium_zz = input$maint_premium_ss , seguro_defl_rate_zz = 0.96 ) calculate_inc_exp_fun( partial_table , loan_term_zz = input$duration , grace_period_zz = input$grace_period , risk_free_rate_zz=0.04 , albedo_wacc_zz = 0.09 ) }) kpi_data <- reactive({ get_kpis(cash_flow_data()) }) # --- Score Cards --- output$retail_price_box <- renderText({ proj <- selected_project() costo_activo <- project_cost_up() markup2 <- round(((input$retail_price /costo_activo ) -1 )*100,2) #glue::glue("${(1 - input$pct / 100) * 70} Billion") paste0("Markup: " , formatC(markup2, format="f", big.mark=",", digits = 2), "%" , "
Retail Price: $", formatC(input$retail_price, format = "f", big.mark = ",", digits=0)) }) output$monthly_payment_box <- renderText({ mp <- kpi_data() |> filter(KPI == "Monthly.Payment") |> pull(`Total QB`) paste0("$",formatC(mp[1], format = "f", big.mark = ",", digits=2)) }) # output$impact_score_box <- renderValueBox({ # proj <- selected_project() # proj$impact_score # }) output$irr_box <- renderText({ mp <- kpi_data() |> filter(KPI == "IRR") |> pull(`Total QB`) paste0(formatC(mp[1], format = "f", big.mark = ",", digits=2),"%") }) # --- Tables --- output$client_table <- renderTable({ proj <- selected_project() proj[, c("client_name", "women_led", "non_profit", "rural_area", "youth_led", "educational_institution", "impoverished_area", "country_name", "department_name", "municipality_name")] }) output$project_table <- renderTable({ proj <- selected_project() proj[, c("project_reference", "project_date", "sale_type", "status", "provider_name", "installed_potential_kw", "project_cost_partner_contract_currency", "partner_contract_currency", "retail_price_project_currency", "project_currency")] }) output$kpi_table <- renderTable({ kpi_data() }) output$cash_flow_table <- renderTable({ cash_flow_data() }) output$summary_table <- renderTable({ cash_flow_data() |> summarize( , payment = sum(payment) , principal = sum(principal) , interest = sum(interest) , enganche = sum(enganche) , legal_fees = sum(legal_fees) , op_de_comp = sum(op_de_comp) , cost_seguro = sum(cost_seguro) , cost_maint = sum(cost_maint) , other_costs = sum(other_costs) , seguro_pymnt = sum(seguro_pymnt) , maint_pymnt = sum(maint_pymnt) , debt_cost = sum(debt_cost) , debt_cost_qb = sum(debt_cost_qb) , iva = sum(iva) , iva_payment_qb = sum(iva_payment_qb) , cost_iva = sum(cost_iva) , cost_iva_qb = sum(cost_iva_qb) ) }) } shinyApp(ui, server)
